# 🗓️ **3-Month Plan: March–May 2025**  
**Goal:** Secure a System Administration job before June 2025.

---

## **March 2025: Build Practical System Admin Skills**  
**Focus:** Hands-on experience with Windows Server, Active Directory, Intune, Networking, VMware, and Security Policies.

---

### **Week 1 (March 1 - March 7): Windows Server & Active Directory**  
- **✅ Key Goals:**  
  - Enroll in **[Windows Server Administration Fundamentals](https://www.coursera.org/learn/windows-server-administration)** (Coursera course).  
  - Set up a **Windows Server 2022 VM** in VMware Workstation or VirtualBox.  
  - Configure Active Directory (AD):  
    - Create a **domain controller (DC)**.  
    - Add **user accounts**, **groups**, and **organizational units (OU)**.  
    - Apply **Group Policies** (disable USB, enforce password policies, restrict software installation).  
  - Learn basic **PowerShell commands** for AD management.  
- **🔹 Hands-On Activities:**  
  - 🎥 Watch: **[Active Directory for Beginners (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k4uODoWQO2U)**.  
  - 💻 Practice: Set up **Remote Desktop Services (RDP)** to manage AD remotely.

---

### **Week 2 (March 8 - March 14): Intune & Microsoft 365 Administration**  
- **✅ Key Goals:**  
  - Take **[Managing Microsoft 365 (Intune & Security)](https://www.coursera.org/learn/microsoft-365)** (Coursera course).  
  - Set up a **Microsoft 365 Developer Tenant** → **[Sign up for free (90 days)](https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-365/dev-program)**.  
  - Configure Intune (**Microsoft Endpoint Manager**):  
    - Enroll a **Windows 10/11 device** in Intune.  
    - Deploy **BitLocker encryption**, password policies, and compliance policies.  
    - Manage software deployments (**Office 365, third-party apps**).  
  - Explore **Azure AD vs. On-Prem AD** and try **Hybrid Azure AD Join**.  
- **🔹 Hands-On Activities:**  
  - 🎥 Watch: **[Microsoft Intune Full Course (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fW2v0_YZ9Eg)**.  
  - 💻 Practice: Apply **Conditional Access Policies** in Intune.

---

### **Week 3 (March 15 - March 21): Networking & VMware Basics**  
- **✅ Key Goals:**  
  - Take **[Computer Networking Basics](https://www.coursera.org/learn/computer-networking-basics)** (Coursera course).  
  - Install **VMware Workstation** and set up a virtual **Windows Server VM**.  
  - Explore VMware features:  
    - **vMotion**, **snapshots**, and **virtual networks**.  
  - Learn networking for a system admin role:  
    - Set up a **DHCP & DNS server**.  
    - Configure **firewall rules & VLANs** in VMware.  
  - Study **RAID**, **NAS**, and **SAN basics**.  
- **🔹 Hands-On Activities:**  
  - 🎥 Watch: **[VMware Basics for Beginners (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c-7p6GOnYfM)**.  
  - 💻 Practice: Set up a **virtualized Active Directory** using VMware.

---

### **Week 4 (March 22 - March 31): Security & User Provisioning**  
- **✅ Key Goals:**  
  - Take **[Windows Server Security & Hardening](https://www.coursera.org/learn/windows-server-security-hardening)** (Coursera course).  
  - Focus on **User Provisioning & Identity Management**:  
    - Automate user creation in AD using **PowerShell scripts**.  
    - Implement **Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)**.  
  - Learn Windows Security & Patch Management:  
    - Configure **Windows Defender**, **MFA**, and **endpoint security measures**.  
    - Set up **Windows Update policies** and **BitLocker encryption**.  
  - Learn **Backup & Disaster Recovery**:  
    - Install **Veeam Backup** and practice server snapshots.  
- **🔹 Hands-On Activities:**  
  - 🎥 Watch: **[Windows Server Security Hardening (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AO0F2E_QZ-k)**.  
  - 💻 Practice: Create a **user provisioning PowerShell script**.

---

## **April 2025: Applying for Jobs & Mock Interviews**  
**Focus:** Improve resume, LinkedIn profile, and job application strategy. Apply for System Admin & IT Support jobs.

---

### **Week 5 (April 1 - April 7): Resume, LinkedIn & Job Applications**  
- **✅ Key Goals:**  
  - Take **[How to Write an Effective Resume](https://www.coursera.org/learn/effective-resume-writing)** (Coursera course).  
  - Optimize LinkedIn Profile:  
    - Add keywords (**System Administrator, Active Directory, Intune, VMware**).  
    - Connect with IT recruiters & hiring managers.  
  - Apply for at least **15–20 jobs** per week.  
- **🔹 Hands-On Activities:**  
  - 🎥 Watch: **[How to Write a Perfect IT Resume (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RkwLO0guS3g)**.  
  - 💻 Practice: Send **3 personalized LinkedIn connection requests** to IT professionals.

---

### **Week 6 (April 8 - April 14): Technical Interview Prep**  
- **✅ Key Goals:**  
  - Take **[Technical Support Fundamentals](https://www.coursera.org/learn/technical-support-fundamentals)** (Coursera course).  
  - Practice common system admin interview questions:  
    - **Active Directory:** “How do you troubleshoot a login failure?”  
    - **Intune:** “How do you enforce company security policies?”  
    - **VMware:** “How do you migrate a VM from one host to another?”  
    - **Storage:** “What’s the difference between RAID 0, 1, and 5?”  
  - Schedule mock interviews via LinkedIn or IT forums.  
  - Apply for **20+ more jobs**, focusing on regional areas for PR eligibility.  
- **🔹 Hands-On Activities:**  
  - 🎥 Watch: **[System Admin Interview Questions & Answers (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O7sHg1Pr2Gs)**.  
  - 💻 Practice: Simulate an interview with ChatGPT.

---

### **Week 7 & 8 (April 15 - April 30): Continued Job Hunting & Experience**  
- **✅ Key Goals:**  
  - Apply for entry-level **IT support roles** to gain real-world experience.  
  - Keep doing mock interviews.  
  - Join IT networking events, LinkedIn groups, and **tech meetups**.

---

## **May 2025: Full Job Search Mode**  
**Focus:** Get interviews, negotiate offers, and secure a job before June.

---

### **Week 9 & 10 (May 1 - May 15): Final Interview Prep**  
- **✅ Key Goals:**  
  - Fine-tune your resume and cover letters based on feedback.  
  - Schedule informational calls with recruiters or professionals in your network.  
  - Apply for another **20+ jobs weekly**, targeting regional areas that offer PR pathways.  
  - Ask for feedback if rejected and adjust your application strategy accordingly.

---

### **Week 11 & 12 (May 16 - May 31): Secure a Job Offer**  
- **✅ Key Goals:**  
  - Focus entirely on attending interviews and negotiating job offers.  
  - Accept a job offer before June 1.  
  - Plan any necessary relocation and prepare to start your first IT job in Australia.

---

🎯 **Milestone Goals:**  
- By March 31: Hands-on experience with key System Admin tools.  
- By April 30: Actively applying for jobs and doing interviews.  
- By May 31: Secure a job offer in System Administration.
